> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash
and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Peel and mince or grate
@garlic{1%clove}. Peel @red onion{1}(peeled and halved); slice into ½-inch-thick
wedges. Finely chop a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings).
Dice @sweet potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Toss Brussels sprouts on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings),
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to
the sheet then).

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
@Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, half the chopped onion, and @water{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP
for 4 servings); season generously with salt (we used ½ tsp; 1 tsp for 4) and
pepper.

Form pork mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4); flatten tops.

Once Brussels sprouts have roasted 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully
place meatloaves on opposite side of baking sheet.

On a second baking sheet, toss sweet potato and onion wedges with a drizzle of
oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast Brussels sprouts and meatloaves on top rack and sweet potatoes and onion
wedges on middle rack until meatloaves are cooked through and veggies are
lightly browned, ~{18-20%minutes}.

== Balsamic-Plum Glaze ==

While everything roasts, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add remaining chopped onion and cook, stirring occasionally,
until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}; cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has
absorbed, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4 servings), @plum jam{2%unit}, @chicken stock
concentrate{1%unit}, @salt{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4), and pepper. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until glaze begins to thicken, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

== To Serve ==

Transfer meatloaves to a #cutting board{} and let cool for ~{1%minute}; slice
crosswise.

Divide meatloaves and veggies between plates. Spoon balsamic glaze over
meatloaves and serve.